website_summaries.verdict: A top key lock box designed for easy use and operation for kids and young adults.
pros: Large combination buttons make it easy to put in the code on the go
Durable enough to be kept outside and can attach to flat surfaces like walls
cons: 5 number lock combinations can be difficult to remember and enter in a timely manner

customer_reviews.title: Great product instructions could have been clearer
customer_reviews.text: I've included the graphic that explains how to set the combo. If it is as unclear to you as it was to me I'll save you some frustration Take the plastic card off the back of the cover Using the tab on that plastic piece as a screw driver turn the screws that correspond to you combos 180 degrees When you are done the nearly invisible arrows on the numbers to your combo should be pointing down.
customer_reviews.author: Gretchen Saunders Swanson

customer_reviews.title: I had a lock box like this when I was growing up and it worked ...
customer_reviews.text: I had a lock box like this when I was growing up and it worked well for years - when we moved, I thought we would get the same kind in case we ever needed it - after a month of it sitting underneath a covered outdoor sofa away from the elements, the day came where I accidentally left my keys at work and biked home - unfortunately, checking multiple times that the locked worked a month earlier, the lock would not open with the appropriate code - the mechanism couldn't even clear. So now I have a box that is holding my keys hostage which rather defeats the purpose.
customer_reviews.author: A M Hayes

customer_reviews.title: NOT EVEN REMOTELY SECURE as a house key lock box.
customer_reviews.text: the open combination is not order of numbers set. you put 5 to 8 numbers, lock the box , press the preset numbers any sequence, door pops open. check out you tube how to open without knowing combination. I DID DUPLICATE IT by opening door without knowing combo. BOTTOM LINE, if you need even a low secure box, buy the rotating tumbler type. I am out the money for this worthless item, because of enlarging-g the mount holes, for most secure mounting. before learning it is worthless.
customer_reviews.author: L. Cadorette

customer_reviews.title: Breaks easy
customer_reviews.text: After screwing this into the wall my wife went to try and put the door on. She found it a little clunky and hard to use while putting the door back on. While trying, she dropped it and the lower black slider broke right off. It's now useless. Wasn't even up for 5 minutes. Oh, one other thing. While there are 10 push buttons, the order that they are pressed doesn't matter. So a combination of 652 is the same as a combination of 625, 256, 265, 526, and 562.
customer_reviews.author: K. Gerber

customer_reviews.title: No more hiding keys unprotected anymore!
customer_reviews.text: I never felt comfortable hiding keys around the outside of our home unprotected... Everyone knows to look by the electric meter, planter or under the door mat right? Haha anyways I decided to install the lock box between my front door and storm door on the lower hinge side of the frame and have it rest on the top of the storm door closer bracket for extra strength. I used longer screws to bite into the 2 x 4 framing and by choosing this location I won’t need to buy the weatherproof boot ;) I should of done this years ago but better late then never!
customer_reviews.author: scott

customer_reviews.title: This is a must for a truely safe to hide-a-key!
customer_reviews.text: Looking for a perfect spot to hide-a-key? Make one with this box. These little boxes, which now have a variety of colors, are Solid, can be re-coded, and are kid friendly as 5 year could use it. I use it to guard our house key in hiding, my business key in hiding and recently bought one for a friend so they could stop hiding theirs under a rug. That is a horrible spot to secure access to a beautiful beach home or any home....and thieves all know it! So make a change for a safer location. It's well worth the peace of mind.
customer_reviews.author: Valentino & Heidi Mallare

customer_reviews.title: lock works great can't ever open it, ever.
customer_reviews.text: i installed it tested it and it worked fine. half way through the winter i locked myself out the box was frozen and has not worked in 2 years. if i could get it off id throw it away.
customer_reviews.author: Michael Ormond

customer_reviews.title: Only 582 combinations! Can brute force in 20 minutes.
customer_reviews.text: Completely useless, as the order of the combination doesn't matter - nowhere does it say this and it's reasonable to assume that the order of the passcode would matter. You can set passcodes with length 5, 6 or 7 - therefore the number of combinations is 10 combinate 5 + 10 combinate 6 + 10 combinate 7 = 582. This is 20x less than a simple four digit lock. If each guess took 2 seconds, you could brute force any combination in less than 20 minutes. A total joke.
customer_reviews.author: Fifthmarch

customer_reviews.title: Very bad design
customer_reviews.text: The door is not hinged and it seems like it should be. When you push the button down the door just comes off in your hand which is weird. And it's heavy. I bought it for AirBnB guests but I'm afraid they won't expect the thing to come off and might drop it. Also when you push the buttons it seems very flimsy. Lastly, the numbers are tiny and the same color as the metal so impossible to see, especially in the dark when people will be checking in. It's useless junk. I wish I had returned it.
customer_reviews.author: Anna

customer_reviews.title: Awkward to use
customer_reviews.text: This unit is solidly built and will do what it says it will do. However, I found it inconvenient that the door comes off in your hand, then you have to get the key with your other hand, then you need two hands to position the door in the right place, set the code, and close it. The door can be easily dropped, which in my case is over concrete, and be damaged. If you are carrying something in your other hand, you must set it down to operate this lock box. I am returning this and getting one where the door is hinged, cannot be dropped, and can be opened and closed with one hand.
customer_reviews.author: Bert Mull

customer_reviews.title: Not a bad keybox for the price
customer_reviews.text: Wanted a more secure way to store a spare key near our door incase we ever loose our keys. The construction seems pretty solid. It would definitely take some serious force to get this thing open without the combination. Also the buttons are mechanical not digital like I almost was expecting so no batteries are required which is a plus. I would have liked a light to that goes from red to green indicate the code unlocks the box. That would require a battery though which probably wouldn't fit in the design. Also would have been nice if the numbers were glow in the dark to be able to see them better at night.
customer_reviews.author: Sgt. Slab Wrankle Top Contributor: Cycling

customer_reviews.title: One star off for simple combination feature
customer_reviews.text: I wanted to have some security on my hidden key, so I added this to my hiding spot. I like how sturdy this think is, and the mechanism works very cleanly. However, I don't love that you can't give it a more complex combination, or make it so the numbers must be pressed in a certain sequence. Knocking a star off for that. But it's very solid, and if you are looking to up the security on your hidden key, this is the right product.
customer_reviews.author: Rabid Reader

customer_reviews.title: Wonderful Product
customer_reviews.text: I purchased this for a secure way to store a spare house key. Having one in a false sprinkler head or other still left the option for someone finding it and gaining entry to my house. This option I store in my garage and even if someone finds it, they won't get into it. It was very easy to set the combination, only downside is you can't use the same number more than once in your combination. I am super excited about this.
customer_reviews.author: Kristy Mecum

customer_reviews.title: should have done this long ago!
customer_reviews.text: I often go running or riding my bike and I hate having to stash my key somewhere either on my person, or hide it somewhere. This solves the problem. Plus - now I really can't lock myself out of the house! I could also grant access if necessary to a family member or neighbor if necessary. Am kind of leery of electronic and wifi locks, so I went old-school with this one. Can't speak to weatherproof qualities as it is on the jamb between storm door and house door. As far as security goes, I used 3 1/2" screws. I REALLY don't think anyone will be able to remove this without tearing my door frame apart!
customer_reviews.author: Richard Witt

customer_reviews.title: Excellent keysafe. Not weatherproofed. 1024 possible combinations. Very rugged and secure.
customer_reviews.text: I’ve had one of these for about 25 years and it still works great and looks like new. I recommend mounting it where it’s protected from rain, since it isn’t weather sealed. It seems very well made and secure. It’s true that the order that buttons are pushed doesn’t matter, but 10 buttons give you 2^10=1024 possible combinations. A determined burglar with that much time would probably pick the lock or look for another way in.
customer_reviews.author: Telllekstr

customer_reviews.title: Got this to provide access control to a key for ...
customer_reviews.text: Got this to provide access control to a key for a supply cabinet. Bolted to the wall it serves it's purpose. Only potential problem I see is, the back of the button pad comes off to access the little cams to set the combination. Someone can be mischievous and pull the card off and reset the combo to whatever they want to. That card should have been a metal plate with allen or torx screws. Other thing is you have to punch the code in again to relock the keypad into the box.
customer_reviews.author: Jimmy James

customer_reviews.title: Broke in less than 2 years and (maybe) a dozen uses
customer_reviews.text: One of the keys ( the 6 key) started sticking almost immediately. Broke in less than 2 years and (maybe) a dozen uses. Now it's on the exterior wall and I can't even get it open to replace it. I have always had great luck with Kiddie products, but this one has been a bad experience.
customer_reviews.author: AnnieK

customer_reviews.title: Kidde 2-Key lock box.
customer_reviews.text: Works great. Would be very difficult to open. However, it is more for convenience than security but it would take the right tools and make a lot of noise to open. Most burglers are interested in speed and don't carry sledge hammers or pinch bars in their pockets. The printed directions are impossible to understand so I went on-line and found a YouTube presentation on how to set the lock. Then I did it in seconds. I would recommend it.
customer_reviews.author: Gulliver

customer_reviews.title: Recommend! I own two.
customer_reviews.text: I actually own two of these Kidde key locks. I bought my first one a year ago and it’s been working great with no issues. I bought this one as an extra to keep just in case the first fails, because I’m a worry bee like that! But for the price, you really can’t go wrong with this. It’s veey basic, very easy to change the codes and unlock to access your key(s). Also, installation is very easy. Just a couple of screws which is comes with, and you’re set!
customer_reviews.author: Ash B

customer_reviews.title: Not a great purchase
customer_reviews.text: Got this to mount on the outside door molding of my elderly mother's condo in case she finds herself locked out by accident. Several things about this product are not ideal.. The first is that the face plate that comes off (in order to retrieve the keys) is fairly heavy, and if were to fall on her foot, she just might wind up with a 0broken bone. Second, the spring mechanism used to release the face plate was difficult for her to use. She has arthritis and the spring proved to be too tight.
customer_reviews.author: Scott

customer_reviews.title: Works well but numbers impossible to see
customer_reviews.text: This lockbox gets the job done reliably however I wish the numbers were painted in a contrasting color. Once you realize that the numbering runs vertically in two columns you can just count the number of buttons to find the correct one to push, however for our vacation rental guests who show up to the property for the first time at the end of a long day to use this lockbox, not being able to see the numbers can be very frustrating.
customer_reviews.author: Lulusmom

customer_reviews.title: Very simple to use and does the job. You ...
customer_reviews.text: Very simple to use and does the job. You turn the dial to set combo and put your keys in. Only flaw would be the combo doesnt have to be in sequence. Ex. If you do 1234. Then 4321, 3214, 1243, etc it will open the lock. I wouldnt use it for anything that requires high security. I just use it to lock front gate but to keep key handy if landscapers come and im not available.
customer_reviews.author: GadgetsnMore

customer_reviews.title: Great product! I was a little disappointed in that ...
customer_reviews.text: Great product! I was a little disappointed in that the door is not hinged. The first time using it, I thought it was hinged and it fell out onto the concrete. Fortunately it did not break. It has room for more than one keys. The other drawback is that you have to have good eyes to see which way the arrows are pointing. It was a good thing I tested the lock before re-inserting the door because I didn't see which way the arrows were pointing and I thought I had it set but the lock wouldn't open. Eventually I saw the arrows and finally got it right.
customer_reviews.author: M. A. Anderson

customer_reviews.title: It really is nice not worrying about leaving a key readily visible under ...
customer_reviews.text: Works exactly as advertised. I did not mount it to a wall, but instead have the unit sitting inside of a decoration at my house for dog walkers to access a key while I am not there. It really is nice not worrying about leaving a key readily visible under the welcome mat.
customer_reviews.author: jrose

customer_reviews.title: Not Secure--Be Careful
customer_reviews.text: I bought this and then did some additional research about its security level. Found many internet instructions on how to easily break into them by manipulating to open (finding the code). I returned this and took off the existing boxes I had.
customer_reviews.author: Bokworm

customer_reviews.title: AWFUL, CAN'T SET CODE, WHOLE FRONT DETACHES..?? Can't even SEE the lines they talk about to adjust!
customer_reviews.text: Rubbish! AWFUL Can't see the markings they're talking about to set the code on the back of the cover, can't understand the directions. Solid, but the whole front detaches. Most awkward! I RETURNED THIS FAST! SO* STRESSFUL. SORRY. TIP Just buy the revolving numbers lockbox. Front stays attached. Cover closes numbers for weather. GREAT.
customer_reviews.author: Margi Normandin

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy, Secure, and Easy to Install
customer_reviews.text: This key safe is one giant hunk of metal. It is rock solid. I hate the idea of having a key outside but with this it feels safe. To my surprise it was really easy to install as it only took maybe 20 minutes. I went with the advice of another reviewer and installed it with longer screws making it much harder to pull out. The only thing to know is that the lock is not a combination lock meaning you just need to know the numbers to unlock it and not the sequence. If you pick 1-2-3 as your numbers you can unlock it by using 3-2-1, 2-3-1, 2-1-3, etc.
customer_reviews.author: BobbyDart

customer_reviews.title: I like
customer_reviews.text: money saver. i've locked myself out of my house. my new door knob will open from the inside even though its locked. i had to break a bathroom window to get back in. $65. the buttons will stiffen in about a year from the weather. it's best to put an electrical outlet cover over them and they will last longer. i put one up at my mom's house. my daughter has one attached inside her tool box on her truck. she moves every now and then from apt to apt.
customer_reviews.author: Andrew B.

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy and tough!
customer_reviews.text: I have 3 of these and all outdoors and one on a boat on the ocean - never an issue and always work and near impossible to crack open (unless you rip them off the base and use a monster saw or sledge to vaporizer the case... LOL! Highly recommend getting the deeper versions so your keys can safeguard more keys or even keys with a fob or keyring of bigger size on it!
customer_reviews.author: HS

customer_reviews.title: Built like a tank but.......
customer_reviews.text: It is built like a tank but it is difficult to re-lock. we have had several occurrences where we shut it but it failed to lock. Also you cannot put more than one key on the ring without making it even more difficult to close. All-in-all it was a disappointment. If you are using only for a rare emergency it might do... but it is not suitable for regular use or by people who are not mechanically minded.
customer_reviews.author: Rob

customer_reviews.title: Must have for homeowners!
customer_reviews.text: oh this is so cool! I basically have it hidden near my house since we always lock ourselves out. I also bought one for my dad and it's really secure, I would not trust anything else. My dad actually wanted to gone one similar to this off of his home since it was drilled into cement. He beat that thing with a hammer and trust me,it's still nailed to the house with a few dents. That box is going nowwhere!
customer_reviews.author: Dommy

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy key lock for permanent installation
customer_reviews.text: I use these -- and give them to my family members and friends. They are very sturdy, impenetrable as far as I can tell. Even if someone pried the box off the side of the house, I doubt it could be opened without using extraordinary means -- blow torch, maybe? They are relatively easy to use -- READ the instructions -- and the combination can be changed without much fuss. Just remember the combination or it won't open. I recommend getting the rubber weather cover for the unit. They don't rust, but the cover is a nice way to keep the lock box clean and free of wear.
customer_reviews.author: Jeanne B.

customer_reviews.title: The combination you pick can be entered in any order and it will still open the lock.
customer_reviews.text: I like the usefullness of this product. It's nice to know you have a spare key incase of an emergency. I dont like that the combination can be entered in any order and it will open the lock box. There is no real security when you can enter the combination in any order and it will open the lock.
customer_reviews.author: Henry Dawson

customer_reviews.title: Never be locked out of anything again
customer_reviews.text: This key box works great for your house, lake house, tool shed, office, etc.. Gave them to my family members and guys on the hunting lease. None have ever failed or been tampered with. I watched a guy on a TV show break into one. It took tools, a lot of time, and some muscle to defeat the box. I change the code regularly and anyone needing in can call my cell for the code. Very, very convenient.
customer_reviews.author: CPA32022

customer_reviews.title: simple a life saver!
customer_reviews.text: love it, simple and a life saver!! The door the town house that I live in auto locks every time that it closes, and many times I've been locked by accident. This key box was the best solution to avoid this embarrassing moments. It is kinda freeing knowing that you can leave your house without your keys, phone, and wallet, and still be able to get a key and go back inside.
customer_reviews.author: SilentBob890

customer_reviews.title: Good way to save a key for the kiddos!
customer_reviews.text: Got this so our kids could get into the apartment when I was not home without leaving a key obviously under the mat. Fairly pleased with it overall. A little bit cumbersome as it’s a little clunky (solid metal front piece) and you have to reset the lock after you’ve opened it prior to inserting the front to close it again which is a little cumbersome. But ultimately very sturdy and works very well!
customer_reviews.author: LP

customer_reviews.title: Good Solution after getting locked out!!!
customer_reviews.text: Easy to install, easy to code and much cheaper than calling the locksmith. This gives you the freedom so you don't have take your keys with you. I installed in the back entry way of house, the install took 2-3 minutes, took longer to get my tools together. The combination set-up took a few minutes once I understood the directions. I read from other reviews about going through all the combinations to get the right one, you have to have some patient crooks to get that done, breaking a window would be easier. This product is very sturdy and will be impossible to remove if you forget the code, unless you remove the entire area where it is installed.
customer_reviews.author: Momar

customer_reviews.title: Never get locked out
customer_reviews.text: We now have two of them. We mounted it with four high grade screws into structure. Someone would need a sledge hammer to get it off or open. If they want to go to that level of effort, then you have bigger problems than someone getting the key. Note that you can’t use the same number twice on a combination, but also the order you enter the numbers doesn’t matter.
customer_reviews.author: David

customer_reviews.title: Ices up in winter, not very secure
customer_reviews.text: Like several others here, I'm very disappointed with this product. Even if you set your combination, pressing the numbers in any order will open it, seeming to me like it would be farily easy to open just by pressing random number patterns into it. Also, when you do open it and use the key, you have to re-enter the numbers again to put the cover back on after you've used the key! Impossible to use single handed, and I've had it ice up in the recent cold weather we've had. I wish I could return it, but I waited too long. Save yourself the headaches and spend $10 more for something better.
customer_reviews.author: Frugal Mama

customer_reviews.title: Very satisfied overall.
customer_reviews.text: With security being an increasing issue hiding a key under the mat just isn't safe any more. I purchased mine over a year ago and with the water resistant case sold separately it makes it less conspicuous and protects it even more. Keep in mind if you're hiding a spare front door key it doen't have to be located adjacent to the door :>). Very satisfied overall..
customer_reviews.author: GH

customer_reviews.title: Love it
customer_reviews.text: I purchased this well over a year ago and the Black weather protector also and I would recommend this to anyone who wants a spare key(s) with easy and secure access. It is pretty simple to give the code and change it if you do not want that person to get access to the key(s) again.
customer_reviews.author: Justin

customer_reviews.title: Better than I was expecting these days...
customer_reviews.text: This thing is solid and heavy. No one is getting into this thing without the code! Spend some extra time to install it right. I like the clip inside you can put your keys on and it holds at least 4 keys if you need it to, maybe more. It will even fit my spare truck key with the big grip end if I wanted to. In this day and age of throw away society I was not expecting this to be nothing more than a cheap plastic or something but it is not.
customer_reviews.author: IAmTheJudgeOfNoOne

customer_reviews.title: Mounted on my shed, no issues through two MN winters
customer_reviews.text: I've had this mounted on the side of my shed for two years now, which means it has held up to Minnesota winters with lots of snow and extreme cold, the crazy rains we've had the last couple springs and no issues at all. The key stays protected and dry, and always opens
customer_reviews.author: james misuraca

customer_reviews.title: Life saver
customer_reviews.text: I have one of these discretely attached to every property we own. Locked myself out of the office one day prior to installing this. Never again! Lets other people access your home or office if needed and you aren't there. Forgot my keys going to the cottage? No problem!
customer_reviews.author: Redbaron2015

customer_reviews.title: A really robust holder.
customer_reviews.text: This is really solid and heavy duty. Easy to program. I mounted by the front door so that emergency services can gain entry if required. Our 911 will link the code to the address so it is instantly available. What I didn't like is the minimum combination is five numbers and these can be entered in any order. Seems to me to significantly increase the risk of a random opening.
customer_reviews.author: KW1K

customer_reviews.title: Just ok
customer_reviews.text: I had a hard time getting this set. The instructions are not very clear. The "arrow" on the screws that you need to turn I could not even see, until I googled online about how to reset the combination. Then I realized it was actually on the screw....Better have good eye sight. Also, like others have said the combination is in ANY ORDER, so it's kind weird, for security purposes. I'm putting in the garage, so it's ok...since someone would have already had to have broken into that first, so I'm keeping.
customer_reviews.author: Andrea F Feltner

customer_reviews.title: Won’t unlock.
customer_reviews.text: Just received it. Instructions are ok. Tested the combo ten times to ensure it worked. Closed door and it won’t unlock. Now a paper weight. :(
customer_reviews.author: Mprhody

customer_reviews.title: Well it will do for to hide a key.
customer_reviews.text: So it is a manual program for combination. It does work but I find the operation a little clumsy. So far when I've need to give the instruction to operate over the phone to new person they have been able to figure it out. Just takes a couple of tries since it's a bit unique. I'm not unhappy just might look as something with easier operation for next time.
customer_reviews.author: Doug

customer_reviews.title: Unable to open, unable to reset passcode
customer_reviews.text: I got a lemon. It wouldn't allow me to set the passcode. It doesn't allow you to reset the code either. Couldn't even open one time.
customer_reviews.author: Chicago customer

customer_reviews.title: Minor inconvenience but still nice
customer_reviews.text: The only thing I did not like about this locking box is the fact that once the box has been opened, you have to enter the combination a second time to be able to close the Box. I was hoping you could just push it closed and it would self lock, kind of like when you leave your house and the door locks behind you. But, before closing it, I have to enter the combination a second time.
customer_reviews.author: Margie Green

customer_reviews.title: Great Value Overall
customer_reviews.text: Very sturdy. Mounts easily. The plastic buttons seem a little flimsy and have a lot of wiggle room when you're pushing on them. It's easy to set and change your combination. The lid completely removes, so if you're not careful it could drop. One idea would be to incorporate a hinge. Wishing for a little more storage space inside. It will not accommodate medium or large keychains. Overall great value.
customer_reviews.author: Adam Wagener

customer_reviews.title: Seems solid, installs in 5 minutes.
customer_reviews.text: Solid, easy to configure and install. I purchased tis to install on a door jamb between two doors where space was tight. Size listed was 2 X 2 X 4 but it is actually 2.25 inches wide. Still fit (barely) but how hard is it to confirm important information before posting it. Off white color blends well with existing paint also.
customer_reviews.author: Tom WTop Contributor: Photography

customer_reviews.title: A nice convenience.
customer_reviews.text: Been outdoors for the past 4 months and it works great. Holds a house key and screen door key-that’s just about the capacity of it. Love that I don’t have to hide entrance keys under a dirty rock or slimy planter pot. Very pleased with the purchase. It would be a great advantage if the numbers lit up at night.
customer_reviews.author: DeeB

customer_reviews.title: Could not break into it
customer_reviews.text: We rented an Air BNB Beach house for vacation. Got locked out so the landlord gave us the code to get into the backup key box, which was one of these. CON: The salt air had seized up the open and reset buttons so the code she gave us did not work. PRO: Even with a hardened steel chisel and 2 1/2 lb sledge I could not break into it. Made a bunch of noise, though. Summary: Keep it greased or lubricated in harsh environments and this thing will keep your key safe. I bought one to replace hers, assuming anyone can ever get it off the wall!
customer_reviews.author: Jason

customer_reviews.title: Works great, nice subtle size
customer_reviews.text: Our old house came with one of these, and we loved having it so much that we had to buy it for the new one. Smaller than the ones we could find at Home Depot, Lowes, etc., which is nice because it's easier to tuck away (so as not to draw attention). This one works great so far, and the one at our old house was at least five years old with no problems. Great to never get locked out of the house!
customer_reviews.author: Caroline

customer_reviews.title: This does not seem like a secure way to keep your keys
customer_reviews.text: This does not seem like a secure way to keep your keys. I didn't realize this until I read the directions to set the code. you can't use a number more than once in your code which really limits your ability to choose a secure code. In addition, say your code is 1-2-3-4-5... well the box opens no matter what order your put these numbers in. So if you press 5-4-3-2-1 it works... 1-4-2-5-3 it works, etc. Other than this, the box itself seems sturdy. This is the only reason I give it as much as two stars.
customer_reviews.author: brewsters

customer_reviews.title: Peace of Mind
customer_reviews.text: This is awesome! I put mine on front porch so i don't have to carry all my keys! To access is simple as push button combo. I ordered another one to attach to the bottom of my truck bumper so that i don't have to go fishing underneath for spare keys when i lock myself out. Solid construction and lets say a thief is inclined to rip it off....they will just have a solid steel box with no hope of opening! This is a must have for latch key kids!
customer_reviews.author: crystal

customer_reviews.title: I have used them on various houses
customer_reviews.text: Ever get locked out? it happens! invariably when you least expect it i but these for each now home i own - and the leave them for whoever buys my homes i put one out front by the garage door and one next to the back door ever need to let someone in - once? these will do that and then you can change the combination in about 2 minutes
customer_reviews.author: josh

customer_reviews.title: Good Lock;  but meant for one key, possibly 2
customer_reviews.text: Works great as advertised, does what I need... Gave 4 stars because it wasn't really clear the lock's capacity inside. This is the smaller capacity, fits a large Master key, but barely fits a 2nd (has to be positioned properly, and when you open lock, the 2nd key falls out). Maybe that's why it's called Kidde...???... I've seen larger capacity ones, which is what I thought I was ordering. But works great, and serves for what I use it for.
customer_reviews.author: CRAB1

customer_reviews.title: Made solid
customer_reviews.text: Took a bit to figure out how to set the combination, but once I understood the instructions it was fine. Nice heavy metal, easy to install. I put it on the door jam between the storm door and house door to keep from freezing. Put it on the hinge side and it is nicely out of the way. Works great!
customer_reviews.author: Tribe Fan

customer_reviews.title: Extremely useful, and easy to reset the combination
customer_reviews.text: I have a few of these lock boxes, one for work, one for our house, etc etc, they are really useful for providing people with access remotely. This combined with the alarm systems really is a great way to let the people in that you want let in, and keep out the people you don't want in. The box can fit 2-3 keys in the lockbox portion, and the code is really easy to set and reset as much as you need to change it.
customer_reviews.author: Samuel Kachmar

customer_reviews.title: heavy duty made BUT top cover comes toally off
customer_reviews.text: Initially I was very happy that the product looks very well made, heavy duty...But what made me not give this item a try was the fact that the top cover comes totally off and as it is heavy it can hurt someone if it falls on the feet and toes... this item is to be mounted on a wall therefore it will fall off when open.
customer_reviews.author: Fernanda

customer_reviews.title: This is a quality, heavy duty box. It's ...
customer_reviews.text: This is a quality, heavy duty box. It's the same one real estate agents used to put on houses for sale before the electronic ones took over. -1 star because the number of possible combinations provides lower security than some other solutions, but I figure if someone is going to stand there all day trying to figure it out they might as well just kick the door in.
customer_reviews.author: Jack

customer_reviews.title: No longer works!
customer_reviews.text: I originally thought it well built but after two years and perhaps only a dozen uses the little plastic button to "clear" it has disinegrated. When I called Kidde the woman said we don't send out parts for "nothing like that"! They offered no help at all. Not a good customer relations method. When I replace my Kidde fire extingushers I'll try another brand.
customer_reviews.author: Bob

customer_reviews.title: Good but small
customer_reviews.text: Not as large as it seems and you'll have a very difficult time fitting many keys in here. Especially if they're longer keys. You could probably fit a few tool box keys. It is weatherproof and seems well built, just small
customer_reviews.author: Sebastian Sutton

customer_reviews.title: Heavy duty little buggers.
customer_reviews.text: We have these at work, and figured it'd be good to keep a spare somewhere for the house or car, so got 2 on a deal w/coupon. Only thing I noticed is that the combination doesn't have to be entered in any particular order... opens as long as all the included numbers are pressed. Not sure if mine is faulty or if this is supposed to be the case
customer_reviews.author: m bar

customer_reviews.title: Live alone you need this
customer_reviews.text: You can change the coating on the lock after giving it out to someone very thick very sturdy very waterproof. I have one key ring with 2 keys on it I suspect you could put as many as 5 to 6 keys on it comfortably
customer_reviews.author: S. M.

customer_reviews.title: Solid and easy to set code
customer_reviews.text: I like these because you don't have to do a rolling combo like some of the other that break/chip your nails to get set or opened. They are easy to install/configure and just work, albeit maybe a bit expensive.
customer_reviews.author: Curt S. Hayes

customer_reviews.title: Adds abit more security while leaving a key outside
customer_reviews.text: Use this to leave a key outside. The case seems to be pretty sturdy but i haven't tired to force my way into it. Needed something with more security for leaving a key outside the house and this has fit the bill
customer_reviews.author: Randall W

customer_reviews.title: Small key space
customer_reviews.text: This was easy enough to install, but the space for keys is so small that there’s barely room for a small key chain. You have to work to position the keys quite flat before you can get it to close. I wish I had ordered a “roomier” model.
customer_reviews.author: L. Davison

customer_reviews.title: Functional alternative to smart locks
customer_reviews.text: I wanted to add a smart lock on my house to allow access by other people if needed, but couldn't afford it, so this old school solution works great. It's inconspicuous and functional and does the job.
customer_reviews.author: LindaYoshi

customer_reviews.title: Looks sturdy.
customer_reviews.text: It's as strong as a safe. Feels heavy and solidly build too. It was very easy to set the combination. You can set a long or short combination as you like.
customer_reviews.author: Hezron

customer_reviews.title: Useless directions
customer_reviews.text: Absolutely terrible. The directions included were completely useless. Bunch of tiny pictures that made no sense. The box locked and would not open. Sent it right back. I do not recommend this.
customer_reviews.author: Donatello

customer_reviews.title: Works as advertised
customer_reviews.text: This is a pretty cool key safe. I planned on using it when selling my place, but ended up selling it before I had to screw this into the wall. Either way, it worked pretty well and I am happy with it.
customer_reviews.author: Customer

customer_reviews.title: Good spare key solution
customer_reviews.text: The Kidde AccessPoint Key Safe provides a safe place for our emergency key. It is sturdy and looks nice. The combination buttons are a little hard to use but and the removable "door" is a little hard to put back into the base but everything does work to our satisfaction. I would recommend the Kidde Key Safe.
customer_reviews.author: EdB

customer_reviews.title: Security is key!
customer_reviews.text: Wish I had bought this sooner. it's really easy to install and use, even my daughter (7) likes it. Our house has multiple people going in and out, people borrowing things, kid coming and going, family cleaning for us, many family members all round. This key lets us store an extra outside without the location changing because someone forgot to re-hide the key and tell everyone else where it is (communication not good).
customer_reviews.author: Snyder Family

customer_reviews.title: Hard to see the arrows
customer_reviews.text: This is a great lock, but to program gram it you had to turn the arrows on the dial, you will need a magnifying glass to see the arrows, or some strong reading glasses, it would have been nice if they painted them black
customer_reviews.author: Ralph Martinez

customer_reviews.title: Solid contruction, but confusing and redundant
customer_reviews.text: It's a good sturdy key box. Setting the combination is very confusing and takes some time and focus. And don;t mess up or you'll be locked out and the key box will be unusable. Also, my biggest con is that you have to reenter the code to re-lock the key inside again. Our box is used frequently and its a pain to have to punch in code once to open then again to lock the cover back into place.
customer_reviews.author: Derek P.

customer_reviews.title: Pretty good.
customer_reviews.text: I'd rate this higher but once open, you have to hold the keypad/front, re-enter the code, and insert the front to close it. It should stay 'unlocked' until replaced. But it is very sturdy.
customer_reviews.author: Kindle Customer

customer_reviews.title: Do not buy
customer_reviews.text: DO NOT BUY instructions different to understand bc mostly pictures AND the arrows are so hard to see. Paint arrow up side with nail polish or sharpie for the future. It is not intuitive
customer_reviews.author: middle school teach

customer_reviews.title: Best Small Footprint LockBox (and cover)
customer_reviews.text: I have always had theses on all the properties I own and find them superior in performance and compact size. With the Weather Cover this box is the best in the market if you want a small footprint and flawless operation. But get the Weather Cover as well as it is designed specifically for the lockbox and is a easy install. The other lockboxes on the market just didn't fit my taste nor functionality. I always tell my locked out friends why not invest in a simple yet effective way to get back in your home when you lock yourself out, which you will do. Highly recommend this product.
customer_reviews.author: Bruce O

customer_reviews.title: Works fine. Easy to mount. Easy to program.
customer_reviews.text: Works fine. Easy to mount. Easy to program. I don't know if it can be hacked or broken into, and I hope I don't have to find out. Also, I just hope it does not have to be used in any emergency!
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Best key lock box
customer_reviews.text: I've been using these key boxes for many years and have not had any trouble. I use them in semi protected outdoor locations, so I have no experience when used in open air environments.
customer_reviews.author: M_

customer_reviews.title: Life saver.  If you lock your keys out or just don’t want to carry the house keys with you.
customer_reviews.text: Love this. No more worried if the kids lose their keys. Easy to use and you can change the code quickly if you need to give access to a person and change it back to your normal name. Fits 2 keys nicely
customer_reviews.author: SH

customer_reviews.title: Defective garbage, very disappointed!
customer_reviews.text: Very disappointed with Kiddle, until now has had very good quality, I have used similar product before and worked very reliability however the 2 new ones are defective, the buttons don't click in correctly on the combo I input, so the lock does not disengage to allow you to open/close the cover.
customer_reviews.author: Tom

customer_reviews.title: Good lock
customer_reviews.text: Works well. We hide our key on ot. Has an attachment to hold keys so they dont fall out. Feels sturdy. Only issue is as long as you click the right numbers, you can push them in any order.
customer_reviews.author: Jessica S

customer_reviews.title: These are good, but mine seem to only last about a ...
customer_reviews.text: These are good, but mine seem to only last about a year before the buttons start to have issues. the big plus for me is the combination is never left in place to show other people (such as a multi-dial combination) and much simpler than a rotary combination.
customer_reviews.author: TheRedDog

customer_reviews.title: Solid!
customer_reviews.text: The screws that come with it are not very long, so we sunk in our own. This is solid. I guess you could blow it up to get the key... seems like a lot of effort though!
customer_reviews.author: Tootsie

customer_reviews.title: Safety must have for home security.
customer_reviews.text: Profession grade lock box. Roomy interior. Easy install. Requires not batteries and ez to program and open for kids. If your kids only have a garage door code to get in the house you need this so they can access a key in an emergency loss of power or if battery fails in opener.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Peace of mind when locked out of the house
customer_reviews.text: Purchased because my mom was locked out of the house when she closed the front door behind her. Fortunately, I work 7 minutes away and drove home quickly to let her back in. Now anybody can gain access through the front door with the correct access code. Peace of mind.
customer_reviews.author: Janine

customer_reviews.title: great key lock box
customer_reviews.text: GET THIS if you have got any reason to leave keys out for - - ohh say the auto dealership's driver to pick up and leave off car keys, a house sitter, a call girl, whatever. It is Weather Proof, no batteries, totally mechanical, and you can change the code any time.
customer_reviews.author: CR

customer_reviews.title: Good sturdy well built product
customer_reviews.text: Good sturdy well built product. Very easy to set the code. Only took me about a minute and installation was pretty easy too. I guess my only complaint is that holes for the screws should be centered on the box so that it is easier to screw them directly into a stud. Otherwise I give this product a full endorsement.
customer_reviews.author: sean

customer_reviews.title: excellent
customer_reviews.text: Once mounted on a wall it's very very hard to get off of the wall with a tool or your hands. It's slightly tapered on the edges which makes it really really hard to. grab if you were a thief.
customer_reviews.author: Large Lau

customer_reviews.title: Could not program
customer_reviews.text: I could not program it. Hard to read numbers. Don't waste your money.. Sent it back.
customer_reviews.author: Sterz

customer_reviews.title: Rock Solid and Easy to Install
customer_reviews.text: This product was probably first designed 50 years ago, but it solves key problems for all time. I have used it in 3 houses, and I love it. I have always installed it on a porch or other covered (damp) space. It should be OK if fully exposed to the elements, but I don't know for sure (it has a lot of buttons/moving parts.)
customer_reviews.author: Prof Atlanta

customer_reviews.title: Decent security
customer_reviews.text: I had one to keep a spare key for 20 years that finally got destroyed by the elements, now with a new one, I shouldn't have to buy another for 20 more years lol
customer_reviews.author: Barnabas O'Collins

customer_reviews.title: Are you sick and damn tired of locking yourself out ...
customer_reviews.text: Are you sick and damn tired of locking yourself out of the house and having to climb through windows? Yeah, me too. I bought one of these and a weatherproof cover. No more destroyed screens and Spiderman imitations. Push the buttons, get your key, and get in the house!!!
customer_reviews.author: Morris Ellis

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy safe
customer_reviews.text: Compared with other lockboxes in this price range this one is twice as nice. Easy to set combo. Not much extra room inside for more than 2 keys so that is only reason to look elsewhere.
customer_reviews.author: christ walsh

customer_reviews.title: Secure!
customer_reviews.text: Okay, so this product is awesome, however, putting it together is quite confusing. I had to call a friend over and we watched a youtube. It truly is fantastic, but just make sure to watch a video on how to set it because the printed directions are wacky.
customer_reviews.author: Lindsay

customer_reviews.title: Secure, easy to use and looks great.
customer_reviews.text: Screwed this to the front door of my apartment right over the deadbolt after I locked myself out accidentally. It looks natural there, and it’s plenty secure. Nobody’s getting into this baby without knowing the combo, period.
customer_reviews.author: Rick
